================================================================================
Architectural Inspirations
================================================================================

L1 - Maturity Assessment Pattern
  Inspired by: FinOps Framework Maturity Assessment
  Source:      https://github.com/finopsfoundation/frameworkassessment
  License:     CC-BY 4.0 (FinOps Foundation framework content)
  Used:        The general idea of a multi-lens, leveled maturity assessment
               with capability-level weighting. Lens names, definitions, level
               anchors, and capability list in this product were rewritten.
  Trademark:   "FinOps" is a trademark of the FinOps Foundation and is not
               used in this product's branding.

L2 - Capability Decomposition Pattern
  Inspired by: CFO Stack (Mike Chong)
  Source:      https://github.com/MikeChongCan/cfo-stack
  License:     MIT with custom LLM-use addendum
  Used:        The general idea of decomposing CFO function into a sequenced
               pipeline of named skills. The phase taxonomy and skill list in
               this product are independently authored from CFO domain
               experience and are NOT derived from the upstream skill catalog.
               To remain outside the scope of the upstream LLM-use addendum,
               this project does not ingest, train on, fine-tune on, evaluate
               against, retrieve from, distill, or summarize the cfo-stack
               repository in any pipeline.

L3 - Multi-Agent Orchestration Pattern
  Inspired by: FinRobot (AI4Finance Foundation)
  Source:      https://github.com/AI4Finance-Foundation/FinRobot
  License:     Apache License 2.0
  Used:        The conceptual three-stage runtime (perception / reasoning /
               action) and a director-routes-to-skill-chain orchestration
               style. No code, class names, or prompts were copied.

L4 - Persona + Self-Grading Iteration Pattern
  Inspired by: jupyter-naas Awesome Notebooks (AI for Work)
  Source:      https://github.com/jupyter-naas/awesome-notebooks
  License:     BSD 3-Clause
  Used:        The general iterate-with-rubric pattern (persona prompt -> draft
               -> rubric grade -> revise until threshold). Rubric dimensions,
               anchors, and scale wording in this product were rewritten.

L5 - Hierarchical Rubric Schema
  Inspired by: openRiskScore / Project Finance Scorecard (Open Risk)
  Source:      https://github.com/open-risk/openRiskScore
  License:     Apache License 2.0
  Used:        The conceptual three-level Group -> Characteristic -> Attribute
               hierarchy with weighted scoring. The schema implementation,
               field names, validation rules, and JSON Schema definitions in
               this product were independently authored.

Reference Implementation
  Inspired by: Financial Planning and Analysis AI Agent (Hassan Subhani)
  Source:      https://github.com/Hassan0397/Financial-Planning-and-Analysis-AI-Agent
  License:     MIT
  Used:        Reference for Streamlit-based FP&A UX patterns. Not yet
               incorporated; will attribute if/when used.

